examples.en: Interfering now could worsen the problem.
The weather has again changed and worsened.
There is some concern that the economy might worsen.
We are now faced with a worsening economic recession.
Spending more money is only going to worsen the problem.
A lot of teachers expect the situation to worsen over the next few years.
The condition of the house worsened with every year of neglect.
Indeed this antidepressant seemed to worsen his pica.
